description:
Clustering algorithms are a type of unsupervised machine learning algorithm used to group data points into clusters based on their similarity. The goal of clustering algorithms is to identify natural groupings in the data and to maximize the similarity within each group while minimizing the similarity between groups. Common clustering algorithms include k-means clustering, hierarchical clustering, and density-based clustering. The formula for clustering algorithms is:

Cluster(X) = {C1, C2, ..., Cn}

Where X is the set of data points, C1, C2, ..., Cn are the clusters, and n is the number of clusters.

