description:
Newton's Method is an iterative numerical method used to find the approximate solution of a nonlinear equation. It is based on the idea of linear approximation and is named after Isaac Newton. The formula for Newton's Method is:

x_{n+1} = x_n - \frac{f(x_n)}{f'(x_n)}

where x_n is the current approximation of the solution, f(x_n) is the value of the function at x_n, and f'(x_n) is the derivative of the function at x_n.

