description:
The Apriori Algorithm is a data mining technique used to identify frequent item sets in a given dataset. It is an iterative algorithm that uses a bottom-up approach to identify frequent item sets by first identifying individual items that appear frequently in the dataset. The algorithm then combines these items into larger and larger item sets as it iterates through the dataset. The formula for the Apriori Algorithm is as follows:

Frequent Item Set = {I | I is an item set and support(I) ≥ min_support}

Where support(I) is the number of transactions containing item set I, and min_support is the minimum support threshold.

